<section class="faq-section">
<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">At what order volume does fulfillment become cheaper than my own warehouse?</div>
<div class="faq-a">For most Ukrainian e-commerce businesses, outsourced fulfillment is cost-competitive starting from 20-30 orders per day. Below that volume, the per-order cost of maintaining your own space, staff, and materials is very high because fixed costs are spread across few orders. Above 500-700 orders per day, very large operations may achieve savings with their own warehouse, but the management overhead and capital requirements are substantial.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">What hidden costs of own warehousing do people usually miss?</div>
<div class="faq-a">The most commonly overlooked costs include: equipment depreciation and maintenance, employee sick leave and turnover costs, electricity and heating bills that spike in winter, insurance for inventory and premises, packaging material waste and storage, IT systems for inventory management, security systems and personnel, and the opportunity cost of the owner's time spent on logistics instead of business growth.</div>
</div>

<div class="faq-item">
<div class="faq-q">Can I switch from my own warehouse to fulfillment without stopping sales?</div>
<div class="faq-a">Yes. MTP Group handles transitions seamlessly. The typical migration process takes 5-7 days: first we set up system integrations while you continue shipping from your warehouse, then inventory is transferred in batches, and orders are gradually switched to the new fulfillment flow. There is no need to pause your sales channels during the transition.</div>
</div>
